{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"plastic wrap, 2 baking trays (30 x 40 cm), baking paper, flower-shaped cookie cutter (6-7 cm), silicone bread mat, rolling pin, pastry brush, lollipop sticks, wire rack, refrigerator, oven","id":"r138842","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-uxLbfbPt-zk\/XZWrQKxo3oI\/AAAAAAAAfkk\/7aNJdi6R9f0IXK2MYOFl6rxChO6dOjn-QCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_hGSBBMtgINAFbHa1.png","title":"Biscuit pops","publishedAt":"2017-10-16T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"content":"130 g brown sugar"},{"content":"230 g unsalted butter, cut into pieces"},{"content":"2 tsp natural vanilla extract"},{"content":"2 eggs, 1 beaten for egg wash"},{"content":"350 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting"},{"content":"100 - 150 g chocolate of choice, broken or cut into 24 thin pieces (see Tips)"},{"content":"icing sugar, for dusting (optional)"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"1.1 g","fat":"10.3 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"9.7 g","calories":"559 kJ \/ 133 kcal"},"preparations":[{"content":"Place sugar and butter into mixing bowl and beat <b>2 min\/speed 3<b>."},{"content":"Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then beat <b>1 min\/speed 3<b> or until light and fluffy."},{"content":"Add vanilla and 1 of the eggs and mix <b>30 sec\/speed 3<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add flour and mix <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>."},{"content":"Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and mix <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer onto a well-floured work surface and shape into a ball. Divide dough into 2 equal portions and shape into discs. Wrap discs in plastic wrap and place into refrigerator for 1 hour or until firm enough to roll out (see Tips)."},{"content":"Preheat oven to 180°C. Line 2 baking trays (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper and set aside."},{"content":"Transfer 1 portion of the dough onto a silicone bread mat or well-floured work surface and roll out (5 mm thickness). Using a flower-shaped cookie cutter (7 cm), cut out 24 biscuits. Brush 12 of the biscuits with egg wash."},{"content":"Place a small piece of chocolate into the centre of each egg-washed biscuit. Place a plain biscuit over chocolate, line up petals and gently press edges together to seal. Cut a small slit into the top of each biscuit. Transfer onto prepared baking trays and place into refrigerator for 10 minutes (see Tips)."},{"content":"Roll out remaining dough portion (5 mm thickness) and cut out 24 biscuits using flower-shaped cookie cutter (7 cm). Brush 12 of the biscuits with egg wash."},{"content":"Place a small piece of chocolate into the centre of each egg-washed biscuit. Place a plain biscuit over chocolate, line up petals and gently press edges together to seal. Cut a small slit into the top of each biscuit. Transfer onto prepared baking trays and place into refrigerator for 10 minutes."},{"content":"Bake biscuits for 10 minutes (180°C) or until golden brown. Remove from oven and gently push a lollipop stick into base of flower biscuit to form a lollipop. Allow to cool on baking trays for 10 minutes, then transfer onto wire racks to cool completely. Dust pops with icing sugar (optional) before serving or wrapping up as a party favour."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Chocolates with a gooey caramel or malt filling work best in this recipe.","You can freeze biscuit dough, simply wrap in plastic wrap and store in the freezer for up to 1 month. Remove from the freezer 1-2 hours before rolling and baking. Proceed as per recipe.","These biscuit pops can be made up to 2 days in advance. After pressing together to enclose chocolate, you can store them in the refrigerator. Proceed with baking as per recipe.","You can find lollipop sticks at cake decorating shops, some supermarkets or online.","Biscuits are best eaten on the day of baking, but will keep for 1 day in a sealable storage container."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","2h 5m","24 portions"]}